Sorry, Enta.
I gotta use the bathroom.

85
00:05:22,733 --> 00:05:24,900
Shouldn't get my hopes
up like that.

86
00:05:24,983 --> 00:05:28,067
[TOI] You realize he's only
going to get worse and worse.

87
00:05:28,150 --> 00:05:30,567
I can see that myself,
thank you.

88
00:05:30,650 --> 00:05:32,442
Wait a sec!

89
00:05:32,525 --> 00:05:35,067
There's a great
cucumber spot over here.

90
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:36,650
You're gonna love this place.

91
00:05:36,733 --> 00:05:39,525
What the hell
is a cucumber spot?

92
00:05:39,608 --> 00:05:43,317
[HARUKA]
Nyantaro! Come and eat!

93
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,400
Hmm?

94
00:05:49,525 --> 00:05:50,775
Well, darn.

95
00:05:50,858 --> 00:05:52,692
Shoulda figured.

96
00:05:52,775 --> 00:05:56,067
We sure came late today,
didn't we? I'm sorry.

97
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:58,650
[meows]

98
00:05:58,733 --> 00:06:00,817
[HARUKA]
Hey, Nyantaro.

99
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:04,733
I'm worried.
Kazu didn't come home.

100
00:06:09,275 --> 00:06:11,400
[HARUKA]
I hope he gets my message.

101
00:06:11,483 --> 00:06:12,942
Huh?

102
00:06:13,025 --> 00:06:15,525
I don't remember
getting that app.

103
00:06:16,608 --> 00:06:19,233
[REO]
Is that a bad boy, I see?

104
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:22,692
[HARUKA]
Hello, sir.

105
00:06:22,775 --> 00:06:24,567
[REO]
Hmph.

106
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:27,358
Did you come here to arrest me?

107
00:06:28,442 --> 00:06:30,233
[REO] Do you want to
make a confession?

108
00:06:30,317 --> 00:06:33,358
I didn't mean to, but I took
Kazu's happiness away.

109
00:06:33,442 --> 00:06:35,025
Kazu? Who?

110
00:06:35,108 --> 00:06:36,942
He's my big brother.

111
00:06:37,025 --> 00:06:39,483
He hasn't come home
since yesterday.

112
00:06:39,567 --> 00:06:42,858
I see. I know that feeling.

113
00:06:42,942 --> 00:06:45,400
I'm missing a special
someone, myself.

114
00:06:45,483 --> 00:06:47,900
[HARUKA]
Are you a bad boy, too?

115
00:06:47,983 --> 00:06:50,108
[REO gasps]
Of course not!

116
00:06:50,192 --> 00:06:52,275
Why, he's the bad one!

117
00:06:52,358 --> 00:06:53,983
He's betraying me again.

118
00:06:54,067 --> 00:06:57,067
With that calm look on his
face, like nothing's wrong.

119
00:06:57,150 --> 00:07:01,942
All his emotions spilled
right out. Like a broken doll.

120
00:07:02,025 --> 00:07:04,942
[HARUKA] I want Kazu
to smile again, that's all.

121
00:07:05,025 --> 00:07:06,775
I see.

122
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,733
Then why don't you show me
what's inside of you?

123
00:07:11,817 --> 00:07:15,358
When I open the door,
what will I find?

124
00:07:15,442 --> 00:07:18,650
Desire? Or love?

125
00:07:18,733 --> 00:07:22,025
The future
can only be claimed...

126
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:24,775
...by those who can
connect their desires.

127
00:07:24,858 --> 00:07:26,025
[NYANTARO hisses]

128
00:07:26,108 --> 00:07:28,608
--Oh, shut up.
--[NYANTARO shrieking]

129
00:07:32,108 --> 00:07:34,858
[ENTA] Come on! You have
to face the facts eventually!

130
00:07:34,942 --> 00:07:36,025
[KAZUKI]
No, I don't!

131
00:07:36,108 --> 00:07:38,733
Haruka has nothing
to do with me anymore!

132
00:07:38,817 --> 00:07:40,275
[ENTA] That's not true!
He's still--

133
00:07:40,358 --> 00:07:43,358
[ENTA yells, grunts]

134
00:07:45,608 --> 00:07:48,067
[KAZUKI]
Nyantaro?

135
00:07:48,150 --> 00:07:50,192
Haruka's gone. Huh?

136
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:53,817
Your dad got
knocked out or something!

137
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,733
[phone dings]

138
00:07:59,608 --> 00:08:00,900
--[phone ringing]
--[KEPPI yells]

139
00:08:00,983 --> 00:08:03,567
--That is not natural.
--[TOI] It's creeping me out.

140
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:06,525
Yes? Hello, <i>kero</i> ?

141
00:08:06,608 --> 00:08:08,692
What unfortunate news.

142
00:08:10,858 --> 00:08:14,650
Haruka Yasaka has been taken
by the Imperial Army.

143
00:08:14,733 --> 00:08:17,192
Whoa, no way!

144
00:08:17,275 --> 00:08:19,692
Uh, what's the Imperial Army?

145
00:08:19,775 --> 00:08:23,650
[KEPPI] The enemy who brought
ruin to the Kappa Kingdom.

146
00:08:23,733 --> 00:08:25,442
[TOI]
Why are they kidnapping people?

147
00:08:25,525 --> 00:08:27,358
What do they do with them?

148
00:08:27,442 --> 00:08:30,233
They're murdered and turned
into <i>kappa</i> zombies.

149
00:08:30,317 --> 00:08:31,150
[gasps]

150
00:08:31,233 --> 00:08:33,025
[KAZUKI]
I won't let that happen!

151
00:08:34,692 --> 00:08:37,233
Come on. Let's save him!

152
00:08:43,567 --> 00:08:46,567
We were expressly forbidden
to act on our own, you know.

153
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:48,900
Ha! You're slaying
me with irony!

154
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:53,192
We shall open a brand
new door for you.

155
00:08:55,358 --> 00:08:58,817
[MABU]
Is it desire? Or love?

156
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:03,567
[REO, MABU]
Desire extraction!

157
00:09:05,358 --> 00:09:07,317
[ENTA]
Otter Empire?

158
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:10,317
[KEPPI] Otters and <i>kappas</i> have
been at war for a long time.

159
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,442
This is merely the
most recent development.

160
00:09:12,525 --> 00:09:14,692
Now follow me, if you would.

161
00:09:16,192 --> 00:09:18,442
[TOI] Why did you have to
drag us into your mess?

162
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:19,858
[KEPPI]
Currently, we are entangled

163
00:09:19,942 --> 00:09:22,108
in a struggle for <i>shirikodama</i> ,

164
00:09:22,192 --> 00:09:25,025
or more specifically,
desire energy.

165
00:09:25,108 --> 00:09:27,358
After crushing
the Kappa Kingdom and seizing

166
00:09:27,442 --> 00:09:29,483
all of our desire energy,

167
00:09:29,567 --> 00:09:32,983
the Otter Empire turned
to humans as their next target.

168
00:09:33,067 --> 00:09:36,358
[TOI] So you're a survivor who
escaped from a ruined kingdom?

169
00:09:36,442 --> 00:09:38,442
--[ALL gasp]
--A survivor who can produce

170
00:09:38,525 --> 00:09:40,317
Dishes of Hope, as you know.

171
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,817
A gift that is mine alone.

172
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:44,775
If the Empire were
made aware of this fact,

173
00:09:44,858 --> 00:09:47,025
they would most certainly
come for my life.

174
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:54,400
[ALL yelling]

175
00:09:57,358 --> 00:09:59,525
[pounding]

176
00:10:02,483 --> 00:10:04,067
Holy crap! What's that?

177
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:06,567
[KEPPI] Welcome to the secret
hideout of the Otter Empire!

178
00:10:06,650 --> 00:10:09,067
[KAZUKI, ENTA, TOI gasp]

179
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:10,733
Where did they take Haruka?

180
00:10:10,817 --> 00:10:13,942
[KEPPI] They put everything in
boxes, so he's in one of these.

181
00:10:14,025 --> 00:10:16,650
[ENTA] But there's a million
of them! We can't open them all!

182
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:18,900
[TOI] Where the hell
are they going, anyway?

183
00:10:20,775 --> 00:10:22,233
[KAZUKI]
Hold on.

184
00:10:23,108 --> 00:10:24,858
[grunts]

185
00:10:24,942 --> 00:10:26,900
[phone rings]

186
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:31,150
--[phone rings]
--[gasps]

187
00:10:35,358 --> 00:10:39,275
[phone ringing]

188
00:10:39,358 --> 00:10:40,400
[KAZUKI grunts]

189
00:10:40,483 --> 00:10:42,525
It's that one!

190
00:10:48,025 --> 00:10:49,650
[ALL grunt]

191
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:54,067
--[ALL panting]
--[yells] Stop!

192
00:10:54,150 --> 00:10:55,400
It's a straight drop down.

193
00:10:55,483 --> 00:10:56,650
What now?

194
00:10:56,733 --> 00:10:59,358
[KAZUKI yelling]

195
00:10:59,442 --> 00:11:01,858
[thuds]

196
00:11:01,942 --> 00:11:03,650
KAZUKI]
Enta!

197
00:11:03,733 --> 00:11:07,150
Just go, Kazuki!
Haruka needs you!

198
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:09,108
[panting]

199
00:11:09,192 --> 00:11:13,108
[alarm blaring]

200
00:11:14,942 --> 00:11:16,317
[grunts]

201
00:11:17,317 --> 00:11:18,483
[KEPPI]
Kero!

202
00:11:18,567 --> 00:11:20,567
--[grunting]
--[gate slams]

203
00:11:22,442 --> 00:11:23,525
[ENTA]
Kuji!

204
00:11:23,608 --> 00:11:26,067
This isn't over yet.
Don't lose hope!

205
00:11:26,150 --> 00:11:27,567
Now haul some ass!

206
00:11:43,942 --> 00:11:47,067
Hey, Haruka!
Your brother's here!

207
00:11:50,358 --> 00:11:52,608
[exploding]

208
00:11:52,692 --> 00:11:54,442
Haruka!

209
00:11:54,525 --> 00:11:57,025
Noooooo!

210
00:12:02,108 --> 00:12:05,442
[KAZUKI whimpering]

211
00:12:05,525 --> 00:12:08,775
It can't be. We were too late?

212
00:12:10,108 --> 00:12:12,483
[KEPPI] Do you truly want
to save your brother?

213
00:12:12,567 --> 00:12:14,692
[whimpering]

214
00:12:14,775 --> 00:12:16,275
You mean, he's not dead?

215
00:12:16,358 --> 00:12:17,692
[KEPPI]
He won't be

216
00:12:17,775 --> 00:12:19,525
if I transplant your
<i>shirikodama</i> into him.

217
00:12:19,608 --> 00:12:21,025
I'm willing to help,

218
00:12:21,108 --> 00:12:23,858
but I would not make that
decision lightly if I were you.

219
00:12:23,942 --> 00:12:25,317
[KAZUKI]
But you can do it?

220
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:28,150
[KEPPI] Of course I can,
and it is the only way.

221
00:12:28,233 --> 00:12:30,150
Hold on!
What happens to Kazuki

222
00:12:30,233 --> 00:12:32,108
after you take out
his <i>shirikodama</i> ?

223
00:12:32,192 --> 00:12:34,608
Will he die like
all the <i>kappa</i> zombies?

224
00:12:34,692 --> 00:12:36,400
Don't let that happen!

225
00:12:39,317 --> 00:12:42,108
The <i>shirikodama</i> allows
humans to form connections.

226
00:12:42,192 --> 00:12:43,358
Without its presence,

227
00:12:43,442 --> 00:12:45,400
their links to others
are completely severed.

228
00:12:45,483 --> 00:12:48,275
They're ejected from the circle
that makes up our world.

229
00:12:49,817 --> 00:12:52,108
Ejected? What does that mean?

230
00:12:52,192 --> 00:12:54,858
[KEPPI] More than fading away
in the traditional sense,

231
00:12:54,942 --> 00:12:56,692
it will be as if Kazuki Yasaka

232
00:12:56,775 --> 00:12:59,150
never existed
in this world at all.

233
00:12:59,233 --> 00:13:01,650
Every memory of you will be
erased and every event

234
00:13:01,733 --> 00:13:05,067
relating to your time on Earth
will be completely undone.

235
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:08,483
That's worse than death!
I wouldn't wish that on anybody!

236
00:13:08,567 --> 00:13:10,858
And that happens to the other
<i>kappa</i> aombies, too?

237
00:13:10,942 --> 00:13:12,817
So we've just been erasing them?

238
00:13:13,817 --> 00:13:15,483
Does that mean...

239
00:13:15,567 --> 00:13:18,650
...Haruka's accident
would be erased as well?

240
00:13:19,983 --> 00:13:21,692
[KEPPI]
It does, indeed.

241
00:13:21,775 --> 00:13:25,442
I'd be gone. That's it.

242
00:13:25,525 --> 00:13:28,650
I have to save him.
Please, do the transplant.

243
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:30,442
[BOTH gasp]

244
00:13:30,525 --> 00:13:32,483
I won't try to stop you.

245
00:13:32,567 --> 00:13:33,692
Muster up some courage,

246
00:13:33,775 --> 00:13:37,483
and you may descend
into the pit on this.

247
00:13:40,983 --> 00:13:42,692
True to my word,

248
00:13:42,775 --> 00:13:46,692
I shall sever your <i>shirikodama</i>
and give it to Haruka.

249
00:13:46,775 --> 00:13:47,900
I'm ready.

250
00:13:47,983 --> 00:13:49,525
[ENTA]
Kazuki! Stop it!

251
00:13:49,608 --> 00:13:51,942
Don't you move an inch!

252
00:13:52,025 --> 00:13:53,817
[KAZUKI]
I get it now.

253
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:57,942
All my life,
I've been outside the circle.

254
00:13:58,025 --> 00:14:02,025
If I was never born,
everything would work out.

255
00:14:02,108 --> 00:14:06,608
This is my last chance.
Even if I can't connect,

256
00:14:06,692 --> 00:14:08,942
I can make things right.

257
00:14:09,525 --> 00:14:11,483
--[clicks]
--[clattering]

258
00:14:11,567 --> 00:14:13,358
You can't do this, Kazuki!

259
00:14:13,442 --> 00:14:16,317
Even if it brings him back,
it's not what Haruka would want!

260
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,025
It's all right,
once this is over,

261
00:14:18,108 --> 00:14:19,358
he won't even remember me.

262
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:21,233
He'll be living
a much better life.

263
00:14:21,317 --> 00:14:22,567
That goes for you, too, Enta.

264
00:14:22,650 --> 00:14:24,525
Soon, you'll forget
all about me.

265
00:14:24,608 --> 00:14:26,483
I am not forgetting you, okay?

266
00:14:26,567 --> 00:14:29,192
You have got to
stop this, Kazuki!

267
00:14:29,275 --> 00:14:31,025
[TOI]
There's no time!

268
00:14:31,108 --> 00:14:33,483
[ENTA]
No!

269
00:14:44,108 --> 00:14:47,483
[screaming]

270
00:14:48,317 --> 00:14:49,525
[ENTA]
Kazuki!

271
00:14:49,608 --> 00:14:50,858
[TOI]
Is he okay?

272
00:14:50,942 --> 00:14:54,275
--I think.
--[TOI, ENTA] Up you go!

273
00:14:54,358 --> 00:14:56,400
[KAZUKI, ENTA sigh]

274
00:14:56,483 --> 00:14:59,358
--What the hell, man?
--[KAZUKI] Why?

275
00:14:59,442 --> 00:15:01,358
Why did you get in my way?

276
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:04,358
It's my life, isn't it?
I can give it up if I want!

277
00:15:04,442 --> 00:15:06,192
The world's better off
without me! Don't--

278
00:15:06,275 --> 00:15:07,775
--[punches]
--[thudding]

279
00:15:07,858 --> 00:15:10,692
Come on. Don't waste time
feeling sorry for yourself.

280
00:15:10,775 --> 00:15:12,483
Think of another solution!

281
00:15:12,567 --> 00:15:13,858
I'll protect you,

282
00:15:13,942 --> 00:15:17,233
even if I have to
protect you from yourself!

283
00:15:19,067 --> 00:15:20,067
[gasps]

284
00:15:20,150 --> 00:15:22,900
But why?
I thought I threw that away!

285
00:15:22,983 --> 00:15:24,733
Haruka gave it to me!

286
00:15:24,817 --> 00:15:27,067
'Cause he never stopped
believing in you!

287
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:30,650
And he's waiting for you
to come and save him!

288
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:33,775
[FEMALE VOICE]
Result: Love. Box: Return.

289
00:15:35,525 --> 00:15:37,108
Look at that.

290
00:15:39,525 --> 00:15:41,317
[KEPPI]
Seems he's still alive!

291
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,983
The box came back up!

292
00:15:45,692 --> 00:15:47,942
Haruka!

293
00:15:51,192 --> 00:15:52,525
[gasps]

294
00:15:53,775 --> 00:15:55,775
[ALL grunting]

295
00:16:03,483 --> 00:16:05,608
[HARUKA] Dear Sara,
I had a lot of fun

296
00:16:05,692 --> 00:16:07,608
connecting with you every day,

297
00:16:07,692 --> 00:16:09,692
but I think it's best
for me to stop now.

298
00:16:09,775 --> 00:16:12,275
So, this is my
last message to you.

299
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,442
[grunts]

300
00:16:14,525 --> 00:16:16,442
[HARUKA]
But, before I say goodbye,

301
00:16:16,525 --> 00:16:18,858
can I tell you
a secret about myself?

302
00:16:18,942 --> 00:16:21,608
The truth is,
I did something bad.

303
00:16:21,692 --> 00:16:23,567
There was a lady
that my brother Kazu

304
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:25,858
cared about a lot,
and I hurt her.

305
00:16:25,942 --> 00:16:29,942
[KAZUKI] You're wrong, Haruka.
This is not your fault!

306
00:16:30,025 --> 00:16:31,525
[HARUKA]
I was afraid she was gonna

307
00:16:31,608 --> 00:16:33,858
take Kazu far away from me.

308
00:16:33,942 --> 00:16:37,608
So I followed him even though
I know I shouldn't have.

309
00:16:40,067 --> 00:16:42,567
[HARUKA]
That day, when he wasn't there,

310
00:16:42,650 --> 00:16:46,317
I picked up something
Kazu's real mom left behind.

311
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:48,525
It smells just like Kazu.

312
00:16:48,608 --> 00:16:51,900
Hi, there! You wouldn't happen
to be Haruka would you?

313
00:16:51,983 --> 00:16:53,900
You need to leave Kazu alone!

314
00:16:53,983 --> 00:16:56,483
Go away!
And don't ever come back!

315
00:16:56,567 --> 00:16:58,150
She wasn't mad.

316
00:16:58,233 --> 00:17:01,233
She just smiled and said,
"It's okay. Don't worry."

317
00:17:01,317 --> 00:17:04,942
She looked
just like my brother.

318
00:17:05,025 --> 00:17:07,442
He never said anything,
but after that,

319
00:17:07,525 --> 00:17:10,692
Kazu stopped smiling
and threw out his <i>miçanga</i> .

320
00:17:10,775 --> 00:17:13,817
I knew it was my fault,
but I didn't want to lose him.

321
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:16,900
No matter what.
I wanted to see him smile again.

322
00:17:16,983 --> 00:17:18,942
He's done so much for me.

323
00:17:19,025 --> 00:17:21,233
I'm so happy
that he's my brother!

324
00:17:21,317 --> 00:17:24,983
So no matter what,
I'm never gonna give up on him.

325
00:17:25,067 --> 00:17:27,108
I know he'll come back someday,

326
00:17:27,192 --> 00:17:30,108
and I know he'll smile
again someday, too!

327
00:17:35,608 --> 00:17:38,275
--Haruka!
--[ENTA] Kazuki!

328
00:17:38,358 --> 00:17:41,858
We can't do anything
from down here! Got a plan?

329
00:17:41,942 --> 00:17:45,233
Damn it!
We made it so far, too!

330
00:17:46,858 --> 00:17:49,358
[clattering]

331
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:54,858
That thing's gonna
shred him up. There's no time!

332
00:17:54,942 --> 00:17:56,317
[ENTA]
Think! Think!

333
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:58,608
[KAZUKI] We don't have anything
to work with!

334
00:17:58,692 --> 00:18:00,483
Please.
No.

335
00:18:00,567 --> 00:18:02,858
Come on, there's gotta
be something, right?

336
00:18:02,942 --> 00:18:04,900
Yeah, like what?

337
00:18:05,983 --> 00:18:08,108
[KEPPI] I know this will be
difficult for you,

338
00:18:08,192 --> 00:18:10,483
but please take this
adorable body of mine and--

339
00:18:10,567 --> 00:18:12,817
[KEPPI grunts]

340
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:14,858
[KEPPI yelling]

341
00:18:14,942 --> 00:18:16,775
Got a pass coming
your way, Jinnai!

342
00:18:16,858 --> 00:18:18,858
[KEPPI]
<i>Kero</i> !

343
00:18:18,942 --> 00:18:20,442
[TOI]
Kick it to Yasaka!

344
00:18:20,525 --> 00:18:22,483
He can stop
the crane if he hits it!

345
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:24,650
[ENTA]
Wait! He won't play anymore!

346
00:18:24,733 --> 00:18:25,900
[KAZUKI]
Enta!

347
00:18:25,983 --> 00:18:27,483
Gimme a pass!

348
00:18:29,692 --> 00:18:31,525
[HARUKA] He can be
a little stubborn sometimes,

349
00:18:31,608 --> 00:18:33,692
but once he sets
his eyes on the goal,

350
00:18:33,775 --> 00:18:35,025
Kazu never gives up.

351
00:18:35,108 --> 00:18:38,483
--Here it comes! You got this!
--[KEPPI yelling]

352
00:18:38,567 --> 00:18:40,358
Thanks, Enta!

353
00:18:40,442 --> 00:18:41,858
[HARUKA]
And even when he's grumpy

354
00:18:41,942 --> 00:18:44,858
or he keeps to himself
a whole bunch, I don't mind.

355
00:18:44,942 --> 00:18:47,858
Because I know he's
a nice person under all that.

356
00:18:47,942 --> 00:18:51,150
Haruka!
I'm always here for you, 'kay?

357
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:53,900
I won't give up!
On either of us!

358
00:18:53,983 --> 00:18:55,900
[KEPPI yelling]

359
00:18:55,983 --> 00:18:57,692
[KEPPI grunts]

360
00:19:04,275 --> 00:19:05,358
[KEPPI]
<i>Kero</i> !

361
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,817
[HARUKA] You act like
you're all alone sometimes,

362
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:19,192
but I'm not the only one who
wants to see you smile again.

363
00:19:19,275 --> 00:19:20,733
Remember, Kazu,

364
00:19:20,817 --> 00:19:23,317
you're in the middle
of a great big circle.

365
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:25,108
[grunts]

366
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:31,025
[KAZUKI, ENTA, TOI]
We did it!

367
00:19:31,108 --> 00:19:32,692
I whiffed it again!

368
00:19:32,775 --> 00:19:35,275
--This totally stinks!
--[bursting]

369
00:19:35,358 --> 00:19:37,650
[exploding]

370
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:39,483
[ALL]
Sarazanmai!

371
00:19:41,067 --> 00:19:43,275
[KEPPI]
Desire assimilated.

372
00:19:43,358 --> 00:19:45,358
[NIOINO ZOMBIE]
Now I'm double-dead!

373
00:19:50,150 --> 00:19:53,067
[MABU]
They stole our target yet again.

374
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:55,900
They've discovered
our hidden base as well.

375
00:19:55,983 --> 00:19:57,900
This error could
very well jeopardize

376
00:19:57,983 --> 00:19:59,317
the success of our mission.

377
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,317
[REO]
It's nothing to flip out about.

378
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:03,275
And that kid
we lost was useless.

379
00:20:03,358 --> 00:20:05,025
All he had was love.

380
00:20:05,108 --> 00:20:07,900
[laughing]

381
00:20:07,983 --> 00:20:09,942
You're laughing. What is it?

382
00:20:10,025 --> 00:20:11,775
Maybe he's not useless.

383
00:20:11,858 --> 00:20:13,817
I owe him one.

384
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:16,817
You see that? That's our hope.

385
00:20:16,900 --> 00:20:18,692
[ENTA]
Okay, forget cucumbers.

386
00:20:18,775 --> 00:20:20,567
--Humans for life!
--[TOI] Agreed.

387
00:20:20,650 --> 00:20:24,192
Hey, uh, I'm sorry.
I've kinda been a jerk.

388
00:20:24,275 --> 00:20:25,775
Whatever.

389
00:20:27,775 --> 00:20:30,983
Sure you don't want
to stay a <i>kappa</i> after all?

390
00:20:31,858 --> 00:20:35,317
It's so weird.
I know I'm the same as before,

391
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:38,358
but I feel like
a completely new person.

392
00:20:38,442 --> 00:20:41,108
This is the real me.

393
00:20:41,192 --> 00:20:42,692
And hey,

394
00:20:42,775 --> 00:20:45,733
I'm glad I have you.
Thanks, guys.

395
00:22:22,442 --> 00:22:25,108
[screaming]

396
00:22:25,192 --> 00:22:26,150
There you are!

397
00:22:26,233 --> 00:22:28,733
[pained grunting]

398
00:22:28,817 --> 00:22:31,608
[KEPPI]
My desire is shattering!

399
00:22:32,692 --> 00:22:34,025
D-D-D-Darkness!

400
00:22:34,108 --> 00:22:36,025
[MABU]
Reo, move out of the way!

401
00:22:41,858 --> 00:22:45,192
Mabu, why? Why would you
sacrifice yourself for me?

402
00:22:45,275 --> 00:22:48,358
[MABU] Let desire flow,
every last drop.

403
00:22:48,442 --> 00:22:52,108
The future belongs to those
who can connect their desires.

404
00:22:52,192 --> 00:22:53,442
Never let it go.

405
00:22:53,525 --> 00:22:56,150
[REO]
Mabu!

